records.addlTxt: 03:04/Rm. 203/PM Defendant Sue NMI Xiong in court with attorney John P Runde.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter by Zoom.  Court calls 22-CF-64 and 22-CF-67.  State would like to proceed with 22-CF-67 first.  Antigo Chief of Police, Daniel Duley, duly sworn on oath, testifies.  State asks Court take judicial notice of Marathon County cases.  Response by Def.'s Atty.  Court takes judicial notice of cases referenced in the probable cause section of complaint.  Testimony closed on 22-CF-67.  22-CF-64/Deputy Travis Krueger, duly sworn on oath, testifies.  State asks Court take judicial notice of Marathon County case and also Langlade County case.  No record by Def.'s Atty.  Court takes judicial notice of those two cases.  State rests.  Def.'s Atty. is not contesting bind over.  22-CF-67/Court finds probable cause.  22-CF-64/Court finds probable cause.  Court binds both cases over for filing of information.  State has efiled informations tracking charges in complaints and has emailed a copy to Def.'s Atty.  3:28 p.m./Recess.  3:33 p.m./Reconvene.  Def.'s Atty. waives reading of informations and enters not guilty plea to all charges in both informations.  Court accepts not guilty pleas and directs clerk to enter into record.  Def. does not need to appear for St. Conf.  Victim rights complied with.  Def. advised to keep address and phone number current with attorney and clerk of court.  Status conference scheduled for August 15, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Preliminary hearing on June 13, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

ADDRESS INFO for Sue NMI Xiong
Current: 740 Jackson St., Wausau, WI 54403 United States  (Effective: 04-14-2022)
Prior: 720 Jackson Street, Wausau, WI 54403
No violent or abusive contact with victim in 22-CF-67.

01:06 PM/Rm. 301/Defendant Sue NMI Xiong in court with attorney John P Runde.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  ADA and Reporter by Zoom.  Court calls 22-CF-64 and 22-CF-67.  Victim by telephone.  Warrants quashed.  Def. has copy of compliants.  There is another case - 22-CF-65.  Def.'s Atty. makes records about that case.  Def. understands charges and penalties.  22-CF-65/State moves to dismiss as that is the same as 22-CF-64.  Court dismisses as it is duplicitous.  State recommends cash bond to cover both files.  Bond arguments by both parties.  Def.'s Atty. advises Def.'s address is incorrect.  Court advises to file a change of address form.  Further bond arguments.  Victim makes statement to Court regarding bond.  Court orders $500.00 cash bond to cover both cases.  1:22 p.m./Recess.  1:23 p.m./Reconvene.  All parties present.  Def. waives time limits for preliminary hearing.  Court accepts waiver of time limits.  Def. does not have to appear for St. Conf.  Atty. can appear by Zoom or in person.  Status conference scheduled for June 6, 2022 at 11:00 am.
